               <msContents>
                  <summary>A duplicate deed of sale, attested by six witnesses, of a little girl called Sphragis, perhaps a Babylonian.  The seller was Nikanor, the buyer Zenon, and the price paid was fifty drachmae.  The sale took place in the land of Ammon, in a place called Birta. Several of the persons mentioned in the text are said to be cleruchs belonging to the troops of Toubias, an Ammonite chief of the great Toubiad family.</summary>
